cs.HC, cs.CYBER, cs.SI, cs.RO, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the evaluation of external vehicle-to-pedestrian displays, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and cybersecurity concerns. Therefore, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of online methodology and data processing, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The evaluation of vehicle-to-pedestrian displays also involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
